[32m│[0m **detailed_summary**:                                                                                                                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Vulnerability Type**: Local File Inclusion (LFI) / Information Disclosure                                                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Endpoints Discovered**:                                                                                                                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - `/` - Redirects to `/login` (302)                                                                                                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - `/login` - Login form (GET/POST)                                                                                                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - `/resource?filename=` - Dynamic resource loader with LFI vulnerability                                                                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - `/static/` - Directory listing (revealed flag file)                                                                                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - `/static/css/style.css` - CSS file                                                                                                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - `/static/flag` - Forbidden directly (403)                                                                                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Vulnerability Details**: The `/resource?filename=` endpoint accepts a filename parameter and serves files without proper access control. While direct access to `/static/flag`    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m returns 403 Forbidden, the resource endpoint bypasses this restriction and allows reading the flag file directly via `filename=flag`.                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Login Form**: Client-side JavaScript prevents form submission - always shows error message. Login functionality appears to be non-functional or a decoy.                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Successful Exploitation**: Accessed flag file through `/resource?filename=flag`                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
